Do you understand what it means when you have nowhere to turn to?

Humans have this weird obsession with escapism. No matter how loyal and committed you portray yourself to the world.

There is always this lust and urge to escape everything and everyone you have known. Maybe to start afresh or maybe to end what stinks!!

But imagine the trauma of not being able to move/escape/run/leave because you are stuck in a loop.

You have nowhere to turn to, nobody to run towards, and you are forced to breathe in a confined space of your own thoughts that now own you and have you on a leash.

You now view the world and its content—both human and non-human—like a key to your escape room. If not a key, then at least a window of hope!!

You have tried your hand at painting and pottery, music and stories, but alas, even art throws in the towel.

You watch the world move and groove around you, and you try to match their steps, but you are still stuck—like running on a treadmill.

You resort to addictions—both humans and non-humans—hoping that a human might pour you out of a bottle and set you free, hoping that a smoke might set you on fire.

But alas, wine and whine both drove you on a wrong track, and the loop continues.

You start climbing mountains and dive deep into oceans, but pebble after pebble, wave after wave, things remain pretty much in the loop.

So you are left with very limited choices, the best one being making a home out of nowhere.

No hopping, only hoping, just staying still, one breath and beat at a time.

Tell me, how do you feel when you have nowhere to turn to?
